  "texts": [
    "It might be objected foot_3 that an ability to answer w-questions is sufficient for understanding.",
    "However, if we only accept answers to w-questions as proxies for understanding, we might lose important information.",
    "While if one is able to answer w-questions, one should also be able to answer why-questions, the reverse does not follow: one might be able to answer certain why-questions, or certain what-questions, and not be capable of answering counterfactual questions.",
    "We argue that in such cases there may still be understanding (albeit in a less sophisticated form).",
    "These forms of understanding become particularly important when trying to benchmark how close certain agents might be to reaching counterfactual understanding."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}